1
00:01:23,584 --> 00:01:24,751
Let's go!

2
00:01:24,835 --> 00:01:26,003
Ready, go!

3
00:01:28,255 --> 00:01:29,715
No issues found with the engine.

4
00:01:29,798 --> 00:01:30,799
Copy that.

5
00:01:30,882 --> 00:01:32,259
No issues found with the fuel system.

6
00:01:32,342 --> 00:01:33,218
Copy that.

7
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:42,763
You're Lieutenant Shikishima, right?

8
00:01:44,730 --> 00:01:46,386
I'm Tachibana, from the Tsukuba Naval

9
00:01:46,387 --> 00:01:47,899
Air Group's maintenance squadron.

9
00:01:47,983 --> 00:01:49,067
Do you remember me?

10
00:01:49,151 --> 00:01:50,485
Tachibana-san.

11
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:51,867
Of course!

11
00:01:52,215 --> 00:01:53,113
Thank you for your help during that time.

12
00:01:53,196 --> 00:01:54,031
Yes.

12
00:01:54,615 --> 00:01:55,650
Wow...

13
00:01:56,381 --> 00:01:59,400
You managed to land that low-quality aircraft

14
00:01:59,401 --> 00:02:01,663
on this hole-filled runway.

14
00:02:01,747 --> 00:02:04,207
As usual, your skills appear to be reliable.

15
00:02:04,999 --> 00:02:07,586
Even though my results in mock ariel combat are good,

16
00:02:07,586 --> 00:02:10,047
going into a real battle with no experience is different.

17
00:02:11,757 --> 00:02:14,723
Luckily, a malfunction in the aircraft

18
00:02:14,724 --> 00:02:15,552
gave you some extra time.

18
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:19,681
Actually...

19
00:02:20,307 --> 00:02:21,368
No matter how hard I try,

19
00:02:21,369 --> 00:02:24,311
I can't find the error you're talking about.

20
00:02:27,773 --> 00:02:29,650
What are you saying?

21
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:54,298
Isn't it a good thing?

21
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,267
That we have people like you?

22
00:03:04,393 --> 00:03:07,521
Even if you obey an order like "go die,"

23
00:03:07,521 --> 00:03:10,190
the outcome of this war is already clear.

24
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:06,591
Give me a gun!

24
00:04:06,591 --> 00:04:07,496
Yes, yes!

25
00:04:09,082 --> 00:04:09,916
An enemy attack?

26
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:10,899
I'm not sure.

26
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:11,585
What is it?

27
00:04:12,169 --> 00:04:13,587
Something big!

28
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:15,172
Is it a new weapon for the US military?

29
00:04:20,594 --> 00:04:21,220
Taki!

30
00:04:21,887 --> 00:04:22,495
Taki! 

31
00:04:23:340 --> 00:04:24,139
It's on the coast!

32
00:04:24,723 --> 00:04:25,510
Copy that!

33
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:39,422
Taki!

33
00:04:39,613 --> 00:04:39,988
Taki-san!

34
00:04:40,071 --> 00:04:41,698
What is this thing?

35
00:04:41,782 --> 00:04:43,282
It's Godzilla...

36
00:04:43,795 --> 00:04:44,201
It's what?

36
00:04:44,284 --> 00:04:45,994
That's what the guy on the island said.

37
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:47,000
He said that on days like today when

37
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,437
deep-sea fish float,

37
00:04:48,437 --> 00:04:48,955
Godzilla will come.

38
00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:50,957
Godzilla?

39
00:04:57,214 --> 00:04:58,632
It's no good.

40
00:04:58,715 --> 00:04:59,800
Let's get out of here!

41
00:04:59,883 --> 00:05:00,717
Run!

42
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:02,344
Run!

43
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:05,388
Hey, hurry up!

44
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:10,936
Hurry! Run, quickly!

45
00:05:13,063 --> 00:05:15,106
What is that thing?

46
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:16,608
We're not sure either.

47
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:19,486
Lieutenant Shikishima!

48
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:20,403
What is it?

49
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:23,657
Can you go over there and shoot it with a 20mm?

50
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:26,076
You're the only person who can shoot it.

51
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:27,994
We're all just from maintenance squadron.

52
00:05:28,078 --> 00:05:31,498
But wouldn't it be bad if it only gets injured?

53
00:05:31,581 --> 00:05:34,376
No living being can survive being hit by a 20mm!

54
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:36,134
Hurry up!

54
00:05:36,134 --> 00:05:37,212
Before it gets within attack range!

55
00:05:37,712 --> 00:05:39,548
Hurry, hurry!

56
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:41,341
Go!

57
00:05:42,509 --> 00:05:43,343
Hurry!

58
00:05:56,982 --> 00:05:57,983
Go!

59
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:14,124
What is he doing?

60
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:23,216
Now! Shoot!

61
00:06:36,980 --> 00:06:39,107
It's coming this way!

62
00:06:39,691 --> 00:06:41,192
What should we do, Tachibana-san?

63
00:06:41,276 --> 00:06:42,240
Ammo!

63
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,570
Get some bullets!

64
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:51,300
Idiot!

64
00:06:51,704 --> 00:06:52,287
Don't shoot it!

65
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:54,259
Stop, you idiot!

66
00:06:55,387 --> 00:06:56,082
Stop!

67
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:01,839
Get out!

68
00:07:02,354 --> 00:07:02,746
Get out!

68
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:03,798
Get out!

68
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:05,133
Hurry and get out!

69
00:07:10,472 --> 00:07:11,765
Tachibana-san!

70
00:07:18,647 --> 00:07:19,898
Shoot!

72
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:39,000
Tomita!

75
00:07:51,137 --> 00:07:52,514
I'll draw it to the front!

76
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:53,473
Shoot to kill!

77
00:09:08,131 --> 00:09:10,133
How could something like this happen to you...

78
00:09:21,436 --> 00:09:22,270
Hey!

79
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:26,149
Hey!

80
00:09:31,196 --> 00:09:32,781
Everyone is dead!

81
00:09:34,866 --> 00:09:36,534
They're dead!

81
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:39,158
Hey!

82
00:09:39,521 --> 00:09:42,126
It's because you didn't shoot it!

83
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:47,378
Damn you!

84
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:27,001
Hey!

85
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:29,003
Hey!

86
00:10:49,566 --> 00:10:50,775
Move.

87
00:11:10,587 --> 00:11:12,380
Isn't that loose?

88
00:11:12,463 --> 00:11:13,298
Yes.

89
00:11:13,381 --> 00:11:14,674
Pay attention carefully.

90
00:11:14,757 --> 00:11:16,259
It's going to be a pain if things keep dragging on.

91
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:17,594
Yes.

92
00:11:25,143 --> 00:11:27,312
Kōichi-san, is that you?

93
00:11:30,773 --> 00:11:32,317
Ōta-neesan!

94
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:34,569
Didn't you go on a suicide attack?

95
00:11:35,278 --> 00:11:37,488
Eh? Is that not the case?

96
00:11:45,163 --> 00:11:47,707
And you came back with a calm face?

97
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,335
Shame on you!

98
00:11:51,753 --> 00:11:54,478
It's because all the soldiers are cowards

99
00:11:54,478 --> 00:11:56,049
that things are the way they are!

99
00:11:58,384 --> 00:12:00,386
If you guys had stayed strong...

100
00:12:01,888 --> 00:12:04,182
...my children wouldn't have died.

101
00:12:13,691 --> 00:12:16,653
Do you know what happened to my parents?

102
00:12:23,952 --> 00:12:25,954
Everyone died.

103
00:12:28,248 --> 00:12:32,043
This area was surrounded by fire.

104
00:12:34,921 --> 00:12:37,006
Your parents too...

105
00:12:39,884 --> 00:12:42,971
Same fate as my children.

106
00:13:00,905 --> 00:13:02,740
"Come back alive."

107
00:13:06,286 --> 00:13:07,912
That's what you said, right?

108
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,014
You thief!

109
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:27,461
Move!

109
00:13:28,809 --> 00:13:29,523
Move, move!

110
00:13:30,310 --> 00:13:31,392
Get her!

111
00:13:31,392 --> 00:13:32,200
Move! Move!

111
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:34,063
Huh?

112
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:35,611
Please!

112
00:13:35,611 --> 00:13:36,566
Eh?

113
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:37,352
Stop!

113
00:13:37,352 --> 00:13:38,401
Stop right there!

114
00:13:38,484 --> 00:13:39,569
Stop right there!

116
00:13:43,114 --> 00:13:44,032
Eh...

117
00:14:12,894 --> 00:14:14,020
Onii-san!

118
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:19,984
Finally.

119
00:14:21,361 --> 00:14:22,820
Onii-san, it's your fault.

120
00:14:22,904 --> 00:14:23,975
I can't come pick up the baby

120
00:14:23,975 --> 00:14:25,782
when you're hanging in an area like that.

121
00:14:26,616 --> 00:14:28,618
Have you been here watching this entire time?

122
00:14:29,786 --> 00:14:34,207
I was getting impatient waiting for you to move, okay?

123
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:38,169
You're hungry, aren't you?

124
00:14:40,171 --> 00:14:42,340
Why didn't you just leave this kid behind?

125
00:14:43,508 --> 00:14:44,509
Hey!

126
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:49,639
There's no way I could leave her behind in that place!

127
00:14:52,058 --> 00:14:53,017
Eh?

128
00:14:54,811 --> 00:14:56,354
Eh...

129
00:14:59,857 --> 00:15:01,651
Please don't follow me.

130
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:03,477
If you leave us here like this,

130
00:15:03,477 --> 00:15:04,821
both me and the child will die.

131
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:06,280
I don't know you!

132
00:15:12,036 --> 00:15:14,705
Once you're done, you're going home.

133
00:15:15,206 --> 00:15:16,547
Scary, isn't he?

133
00:15:16,547 --> 00:15:18,501
Onii-san is heartless.

134
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:24,173
What happened to your husband?

135
00:15:24,257 --> 00:15:26,008
Was he taken into the army?

136
00:15:27,135 --> 00:15:29,720
Do I look like I have a husband?

137
00:15:30,221 --> 00:15:30,628
Eh?

137
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:32,974
Then whose kid is that?

138
00:15:34,559 --> 00:15:36,487
It doesn't matter.

138
00:15:36,487 --> 00:15:37,562
That's not a good thing!

139
00:15:41,482 --> 00:15:43,443
During the air raids...

140
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:46,946
...the child's dying okaa-san asked me to.

141
00:15:49,157 --> 00:15:49,991
So then...

142
00:15:50,908 --> 00:15:53,494
You're not related to that child?

143
00:15:54,704 --> 00:15:55,788
So what?

144
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,501
What are you, an idiot?

145
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:03,590
You're not in a place to take in a baby like that

145
00:16:03,590 --> 00:16:04,464
and live peacefully!

146
00:16:04,547 --> 00:16:06,299
Even you couldn't abandon it, onii-san.

147
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:07,508
Hey!

148
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:14,724
Name?

150
00:16:21,972 --> 00:16:23,316
Your name.

151
00:16:25,902 --> 00:16:26,736
Noriko.

152
00:16:29,864 --> 00:16:32,033
Why do you act like that?

153
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:33,322
If you're acting like you're a vagrant,

153
00:16:33,322 --> 00:16:34,577
it means you're probably poor.

154
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:36,829
Are you telling me to become a whore?

155
00:16:36,913 --> 00:16:38,623
Don't give me that look.

156
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:41,674
In this day and age,

156
00:16:41,674 --> 00:16:42,898
if you're out of options,

156
00:16:42,898 --> 00:16:43,753
then it can't be helped.

157
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:51,052
What about your parents and siblings?

158
00:17:01,395 --> 00:17:02,688
Your parents?

159
00:17:07,068 --> 00:17:08,069
Yeah.

160
00:17:09,779 --> 00:17:12,740
They both died in the air raid.

161
00:17:17,453 --> 00:17:19,455
You and me are the same, onii-san.

162
00:17:38,849 --> 00:17:39,684
Eh?

163
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:40,200
He... 

163
00:17:40,746 --> 00:17:41,100
Hey!

163
00:17:41,298 --> 00:17:41,811
Wait a...

164
00:17:43,813 --> 00:17:45,273
You...

165
00:17:59,203 --> 00:18:00,329
Hey!

166
00:18:02,707 --> 00:18:04,250
What's with that?

167
00:18:05,835 --> 00:18:06,919
With what?

168
00:18:07,003 --> 00:18:08,754
Don't play dumb.

169
00:18:09,589 --> 00:18:11,674
The parent and the child you picked up.

170
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:13,718
Who do you think you are,

170
00:18:13,718 --> 00:18:14,844
picking up people like that?

171
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:15,698
No.

172
00:18:16,729 --> 00:18:18,848
They just showed up and settled on their own.

172
00:18:19,557 --> 00:18:20,781
If you haven't kicked them out,

172
00:18:20,781 --> 00:18:22,476
then you've picked them up.

173
00:18:26,814 --> 00:18:28,816
Hypocrite...

174
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:32,130
I'm not dealing with this.

174
00:18:32,981 --> 00:18:34,739
Sorry for wasting your time.

175
00:18:39,827 --> 00:18:40,661
Ah...

175
00:18:42,455 --> 00:18:43,218
That kid...

176
00:18:43,625 --> 00:18:45,124
Is she breastfeeding it properly?

177
00:18:47,043 --> 00:18:47,648
Ah, no...

178
00:18:48,502 --> 00:18:49,153
She's...

179
00:18:50,270 --> 00:18:51,589
She's not the child's mother.

179
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:54,175
What is that supposed to mean?

180
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:07,980
If things continue like this,

181
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:09,649
she'll die of malnutrition.

181
00:19:10,358 --> 00:19:11,359
Right?

183
00:19:13,736 --> 00:19:16,784
Picking up a child you're not capable of raising...

184
00:19:17,448 --> 00:19:19,283
What on earth is that all about?

185
00:19:20,451 --> 00:19:21,535
I'm sorry.

186
00:19:30,169 --> 00:19:31,796
It's not for you to eat.

187
00:19:33,214 --> 00:19:35,341
Adults can survive no matter what they eat.

188
00:19:40,971 --> 00:19:42,973
Use this to make gruel for the child.

189
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:45,132
Ah...

189
00:19:46:200 --> 00:19:48,312
There goes my white rice.

190
00:19:49,689 --> 00:19:51,649
It's annoying, seriously...

192
00:20:03,244 --> 00:20:05,287
Ah, damn it!

193
00:20:05,371 --> 00:20:06,872
I'm soaking wet!

195
00:20:13,796 --> 00:20:15,256
Did you get a job?

196
00:20:16,674 --> 00:20:19,260
I did find something, but...

197
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:21,178
Eh? What's the problem?

198
00:20:21,262 --> 00:20:22,096
Ah...

199
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:24,724
The pay isn't bad either.

200
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:26,308
Check this out..

201
00:20:26,392 --> 00:20:28,132
It seems that just the preperation money

201
00:20:28,132 --> 00:20:29,311
is ¥3000 alone!

202
00:20:29,395 --> 00:20:31,272
That's awesome!

203
00:20:35,860 --> 00:20:37,111
It has to be a scam.

204
00:20:37,695 --> 00:20:38,375
Just the other day,

204
00:20:38,375 --> 00:20:40,406
all the rice that you brought in was stolen.

205
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:43,284
That's not the case with this.

206
00:20:43,367 --> 00:20:45,494
What's different about it?

207
00:20:45,578 --> 00:20:46,920
It has a stamp of approval from none other

208
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:48,205
than the Ministry of Demobilization.

208
00:20:48,706 --> 00:20:51,000
There's a reason that it pays so well.

209
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:52,418
The reason?

210
00:20:52,501 --> 00:20:53,695
During the war,

210
00:20:55,180 --> 00:20:56,984
both the US military and Imperial Navy

211
00:20:56,984 --> 00:20:58,466
secretly laid down mines, right?

211
00:20:59,467 --> 00:21:00,634
It's a job to clean that up.

212
00:21:02,595 --> 00:21:04,346
But the pay is insanely good, because...

213
00:21:05,222 --> 00:21:06,098
Well...

214
00:21:09,059 --> 00:21:09,732
There's...

214
00:21:10,870 --> 00:21:13,105
There's no guarantee that I'll come back alive.

215
00:21:15,024 --> 00:21:16,525
What are you talking about?!

216
00:21:16,609 --> 00:21:18,402
You just made it back alive!

217
00:21:18,486 --> 00:21:20,289
There's nothinng else we can do!

218
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:21,324
At this rate,

218
00:21:21,324 --> 00:21:22,907
the three of us are going to starve to death!

219
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:24,450
Even Akiko if it keeps going like this...

220
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:29,205
I understand that, but...

221
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:33,000
If we have the money...

222
00:21:33,709 --> 00:21:34,905
If we have the money,

222
00:21:34,905 --> 00:21:37,713
we can even buy powdered milk from America!

223
00:21:37,797 --> 00:21:38,672
For that reason, I'd...

224
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:41,342
It's no good if you die!

225
00:21:45,930 --> 00:21:46,931
It's okay.

226
00:21:48,057 --> 00:21:49,442
Just becaus it's dangerous 

226
00:21:49,442 --> 00:21:51,018
doesn't mean I'm going to die.

227
00:21:52,436 --> 00:21:53,740
It's different from the suicide attacks

228
00:21:53,740 --> 00:21:54,730
of ten deaths and no lives.

228
00:21:59,735 --> 00:22:00,300
And besides,

229
00:22:01,268 --> 00:22:02,400
I'll be on a special ship,

229
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:04,865
so the magnetic mines won't be able to detect us.

229
00:22:09,620 --> 00:22:10,700
This is...

230
00:22:11,355 --> 00:22:12,540
The special ship?

230
00:22:26,971 --> 00:22:27,804
Hey, you!

231
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,640
Are you our next gunner?

231
00:22:29,723 --> 00:22:30,641
I'm Shikishima.

232
00:22:30,724 --> 00:22:31,559
Are you a boat gunner?

233
00:22:31,642 --> 00:22:32,893
I used to be a fighter pilot.

234
00:22:32,977 --> 00:22:33,700
What?

235
00:22:34,151 --> 00:22:35,354
What's this guy for?

235
00:22:35,437 --> 00:22:36,856
You're a former fighter pilot?

236
00:22:36,939 --> 00:22:38,104
I don't want to be with this

237
00:22:38,104 --> 00:22:39,900
wreck of a military shōnen.

237
00:22:39,984 --> 00:22:41,573
Were you disappointed?

238
00:22:42,194 --> 00:22:43,404
