01:07:22,747 --> 01:07:24,457
This time, the person who devised the plan...

695
01:07:24,541 --> 01:07:27,544
...is me, former Navy technical officer Noda Kenji.

696
01:07:27,627 --> 01:07:29,629
First of all,

697
01:07:30,720 --> 01:07:32,767
according to the legend from Ōdo Island,

698
01:07:32,767 --> 01:07:34,300
this monster is called Godzilla.

698
01:07:34,384 --> 01:07:38,930
Godzilla takes almost no damage from normal firemarms.

699
01:07:39,013 --> 01:07:40,306
I saw it right before my eyes.

700
01:07:40,390 --> 01:07:44,394
It even got hit by Heavy Cruiser Takao's main gun,

701
01:07:44,394 --> 01:07:46,312
but it quickly regenerated.

702
01:07:48,940 --> 01:07:50,358
So in secret,

703
01:07:50,441 --> 01:07:53,236
I came up with another solution.

704
01:07:55,363 --> 01:07:56,500
First,

705
01:07:56,500 --> 01:07:57,824
I'm going to show you a simple experiment.

705
01:07:58,408 --> 01:07:59,700
The water in here is salt water with

706
01:07:59,700 --> 01:08:01,661
the same concentration as seawater.

706
01:08:01,744 --> 01:08:04,300
This Godzilla-like wood has a weight attached to it

707
01:08:04,300 --> 01:08:06,833
so that it just barely floats.

707
01:08:06,916 --> 01:08:07,649
In this state,

708
01:08:07,649 --> 01:08:09,544
What happens if we pumped freon gas into the tube,

708
01:08:09,627 --> 01:08:11,754
covering the piece of wood with bubbles?

709
01:08:11,838 --> 01:08:13,631
What happens?

710
01:08:13,715 --> 01:08:15,200
Whether or not bubbles comes out,

711
01:08:15,200 --> 01:08:15,925
it'll still float.

711
01:08:16,009 --> 01:08:17,282
Yeah, that's obvious.

712
01:08:18,636 --> 01:08:19,971
That's what you'd think, right?

713
01:08:26,853 --> 01:08:27,572
It sunk!

714
01:08:30,231 --> 01:08:32,567
The bubbles from the freon gas enclose the wood

715
01:08:32,650 --> 01:08:34,944
and prevent it from coming in contact with the seawater.

716
01:08:35,028 --> 01:08:37,594
My plan is that this time, we use this to sink Godzilla,

716
01:08:37,594 --> 01:08:40,491
the monster that attacked Tōkyō, to the bottom of the sea.

717
01:08:40,575 --> 01:08:41,625
Hey,

718
01:08:42,100 --> 01:08:44,954
the Acedemic is a surprisingly awesome guy, isn't he?

719
01:08:59,052 --> 01:09:00,150
As you know,

720
01:09:00,150 --> 01:09:02,625
Sagami Trench off of the coast is more than

720
01:09:02,625 --> 01:09:03,723
1500 meters deep,

720
01:09:03,723 --> 01:09:06,225
an incredible depth for waters off the coast.

721
01:09:06,309 --> 01:09:07,461
Our current plan is to attach

722
01:09:07,461 --> 01:09:10,188
a large number of freon gas tanks to Godzilla,

722
01:09:10,271 --> 01:09:11,755
and at the same time,

723
01:09:11,755 --> 01:09:13,733
have them envelop it with a curtain of foam.

723
01:09:13,816 --> 01:09:15,28
Within a short period of time,

724
01:09:15,289 --> 01:09:17,290
it will sink into Sagami Trench

724
01:09:17,290 --> 01:09:18,529
and the pressure will kill it.

724
01:09:21,866 --> 01:09:24,160
We'll kill Godzilla with the power of the ocean.

725
01:09:25,161 --> 01:09:25,800
This is...

726
01:09:26,770 --> 01:09:28,706
...the outline of Operation Wadatsumi.

726
01:09:29,832 --> 01:09:31,084
That thing came from the see.

727
01:09:31,167 --> 01:09:33,753
It isn't bothered by the deep water pressure.

728
01:09:35,129 --> 01:09:36,777
According to my calculations,

729
01:09:36,777 --> 01:09:38,375
after about 25 seconds,

729
01:09:38,375 --> 01:09:41,719
1500 tons will be exerted per square meter.

729
01:09:41,803 --> 01:09:44,097
Even creatures that can normally survive in the deep sea

730
01:09:44,180 --> 01:09:47,100
cannot with stand these types of rapid pressure changes.

731
01:09:47,183 --> 01:09:48,059
That and...

732
01:09:49,268 --> 01:09:51,437
Can you absolutely kill Godzilla?

733
01:09:53,981 --> 01:09:57,235
There's a lot we don't know about Godzilla's ecology,

734
01:09:57,318 --> 01:09:58,670
so we can only create countermeasures against it

735
01:09:58,670 --> 01:09:59,445
based on our predictions.

735
01:10:00,820 --> 01:10:02,000
That's bullcrap, isn't it?

736
01:10:03,533 --> 01:10:05,300
However, since artillery fire is ineffective,

737
01:10:05,300 --> 01:10:06,077
this is the best solution.

737
01:10:06,160 --> 01:10:07,115
Can you kill him?

738
01:10:07,115 --> 01:10:08,329
Or can you not?

738
01:10:11,374 --> 01:10:13,292
I can't say for sure.

739
01:10:15,837 --> 01:10:16,671
Shikishima!

740
01:10:17,296 --> 01:10:18,673
There is a possibility!

741
01:10:23,928 --> 01:10:24,929
Shiki-san...

742
01:10:26,639 --> 01:10:28,099
Listen until the end!

743
01:10:45,408 --> 01:10:48,077
Now, for a detailed explanation,

744
01:10:53,124 --> 01:10:55,830
Using two destroyers,

745
01:10:55,830 --> 01:10:57,044
we'll wrap the cable around Godzilla.

745
01:10:58,045 --> 01:10:59,940
The cable is already equipped with

746
01:10:59,940 --> 01:11:03,760
a large amount of freon gas tanks.

746
01:11:06,012 --> 01:11:08,190
As soon as it's wrapped around Godzilla,

747
01:11:08,190 --> 01:11:09,474
all of the foam releases,

747
01:11:10,641 --> 01:11:14,812
and Godzilla is pulled down 1500 meters into the deep sea.

748
01:11:14,896 --> 01:11:16,481
But what if that doesn't work?

749
01:11:16,564 --> 01:11:18,149
Then we have a backup plan.

750
01:11:19,484 --> 01:11:20,800
Everyone,

751
01:11:20,800 --> 01:11:22,403
please look at the courtyard.

751
01:11:40,755 --> 01:11:41,589
Deploy!

752
01:11:47,470 --> 01:11:50,139
I'm Itagaki from Tōyō Baloon.

753
01:11:50,223 --> 01:11:53:983
What you just saw is an inflatable floatation device

754
01:11:53:983 --> 01:11:57,814
inspired by the ones installed on former Naval aircraft.

755
01:11:57,897 --> 01:12:01,236
This so-called floating bag gains buoyancy by having

756
01:12:01,236 --> 01:12:03,110
Carbon Dioxide blown into the air sacs.

757
01:12:04,904 --> 01:12:07,118
Now, this can bring Godzilla,

758
01:12:07,118 --> 01:12:08,444
who will have reached the bottom of the ocean,

758
01:12:08,444 --> 01:12:10,451
all the way back up to the surface.

758
01:12:10,535 --> 01:12:13,104
Even if it is able to withstand high pressure,

759
01:12:13,104 --> 01:12:15,206
I don't think it will be able to withstand

759
01:12:15,206 --> 01:12:17,166
the massive decompression that will follow it.

760
01:12:17,250 --> 01:12:18,400
Of course,

761
01:12:18,400 --> 01:12:21,546
I cannot say for sure that we will defeat it.

761
01:12:21,629 --> 01:12:24,006
But the only thing we can do now is what we can.

762
01:12:29,512 --> 01:12:31,514
To all those who survived the war,

763
01:12:32,223 --> 01:12:35,500
I am sorry to ask you to take on a

764
01:12:35,500 --> 01:12:37,490
life-threatening mission again,

764
01:12:37,490 --> 01:12:38:100
but...

764
01:12:38,400 --> 01:12:39,689
I want you to understand.

764
01:12:40,314 --> 01:12:42,089
Now that neither the Japanese government

765
01:12:42,089 --> 01:12:43,442
nor American government can help us out,

765
01:12:44,151 --> 01:12:45,736
we are the only ones who can shape

766
01:12:45,736 --> 01:12:47,196
the future for this country.

766
01:12:50,408 --> 01:12:51,659
It's impossible.

767
01:12:53,578 --> 01:12:55,454
I have a family.

768
01:12:55,538 --> 01:12:56,818
I just can't do it.

769
01:12:56,818 --> 01:12:58,416
That goes for most people here.

769
01:12:59,208 --> 01:13:00,872
Why are we the only ones

770
01:13:00,872 --> 01:13:02,920
drawing the short straws?

770
01:13:04,338 --> 01:13:06,757
I don't want this to be like the war.

771
01:13:13,055 --> 01:13:14,223
Quiet down.

772
01:13:14,307 --> 01:13:15,786
Everyone,

773
01:13:15,786 --> 01:13:17,059
I want you to listen carefully.

773
01:13:17,977 --> 01:13:19,729
This is not an order.

774
01:13:20,271 --> 01:13:23,316
Those with personal situations are free to leave.

775
01:13:24,233 --> 01:13:27,361
We have no right to stop you from doing so.

776
01:13:51,636 --> 01:13:52,637
This...

777
01:13:54,305 --> 01:13:56,307
We're not going to die for sure, right?

778
01:13:57,350 --> 01:13:58,726
Of course not!

779
01:14:01,145 --> 01:14:02,265
Well,

780
01:14:02,265 --> 01:14:04,148
then it's much better than wartime!

781
01:14:07,318 --> 01:14:09,111
Someone has to do it.

782
01:14:09,987 --> 01:14:11,948
It can't be helped, can it?

783
01:14:12,031 --> 01:14:14,325
Without us, the ships won't be able to move.

784
01:14:14,408 --> 01:14:16,786
That's right!

785
01:14:16,869 --> 01:14:18,731
All right!

786
01:14:18,731 --> 01:14:19,580
Let's do it!

787
01:14:28,881 --> 01:14:30,091
Everyone...

788
01:14:32,426 --> 01:14:33,719
Thank you.

789
01:14:43,187 --> 01:14:44,897
But...

790
01:14:44,981 --> 01:14:47,200
I still can't believe you're the one who

791
01:14:47,200 --> 01:14:48,300
planned this type of operation.

792
01:14:49,300 --> 01:14:51,779
I've encountered Godzilla in real life.

793
01:14:51,862 --> 01:14:54,532
That's why they gave me the green light.

794
01:14:54,615 --> 01:14:58,077
They called us in for the same reason, didn't they?

795
01:14:59,480 --> 01:15:01,080
Do you think it'll return?

796
01:15:02,304 --> 01:15:05,584
Due to just recently landing in Tōkyō,

797
01:15:05,668 --> 01:15:08,671
you can see it as an addition to Godzilla's territory.

798
01:15:08,754 --> 01:15:09,964
Worst case scenario...

799
01:15:10,756 --> 01:15:13,801
Godzilla appears again within the next ten days.

800
01:15:13,884 --> 01:15:15,136
That's early!

801
01:15:15,219 --> 01:15:15,810
Apparently,

802
01:15:15,810 --> 01:15:18,139
they've placed lots of radition-detecting buoys.

802
01:15:18,222 --> 01:15:21,058
We can't soley rely on our eyes to detect it.

803
01:15:21,142 --> 01:15:23,600
First off, if you set a trap for it,

804
01:15:23,600 --> 01:15:24,700
are you expecting it to come up and say,

805
01:15:24,700 --> 01:15:25,563
"Oh, it that the case?"

805
01:15:26,105 --> 01:15:27,189
That's it.

806
01:15:27,273 --> 01:15:28,357
Hey, that's impossible.

807
01:15:28,441 --> 01:15:30,177
Please don't make fun of me.

807
01:15:30,177 --> 01:15:32,319
I'm thinking about it carefully.

808
01:15:34,697 --> 01:15:36,300
There's an loudspeaker that's used for

808
01:15:36,300 --> 01:15:37,575
underwater acoustic minesweeping.

809
01:15:37,658 --> 01:15:39,076
Using that,

810
01:15:39,160 --> 01:15:41,543
we'll play back the recorded sound of Godzilla

811
01:15:41,543 --> 01:15:42,371
from his most recent appearance.

811
01:15:42,455 --> 01:15:43,539
The sound of Godzilla?

812
01:15:43,622 --> 01:15:44,498
Yes.

813
01:15:44,582 --> 01:15:47,305
Godzilla will chase after another being because

814
01:15:47,305 --> 01:15:48,711
it'll feel like it's territory is being invaded.

814
01:15:49,253 --> 01:15:50,087
At least he should.

815
01:15:50,171 --> 01:15:51,589
"Should?"

816
01:15:51,672 --> 01:15:53,466
It's always "should."

817
01:15:53,549 --> 01:15:55,140
And what's even the point of that...

818
01:15:55,140 --> 01:15:56,635
levitation-floating-device-thing?

818
01:15:56,719 --> 01:15:59,513
I don't feel like it's gonna work.

819
01:15:59,597 --> 01:16:01,849
Then what are you saying I should do?

820
01:16:01,932 --> 01:16:02,310
Yes, yes!

821
01:16:03,142 --> 01:16:05,227
How about we use a destroyer to pull it up?

821
01:16:05,311 --> 01:16:06,687
Don't say stupid things.

822
01:16:06,687 --> 01:16:08,439
Godzilla weighs around 20,000 tons.

823
01:16:08,522 --> 01:16:10,733
The thrust of two destroyers just isn't enough.

824
01:16:13,861 --> 01:16:17,239
In a nutshell, your plan is full of holes.

825
01:16:18,074 --> 01:16:19,700
If you're going to say those types of things,

826
01:16:19,700 --> 01:16:21,952
then please provide an alternative plan.

826
01:16:24,205 --> 01:16:25,414
Noda-san.

827
01:16:27,208 --> 01:16:28,492
Do you have any connections

828
01:16:29,562 --> 01:16:30,586
to fighter jets somewhere?

828
01:16:31,462 --> 01:16:32,588
Fighter jets?

829
01:16:32,671 --> 01:16:34,799
In the unlikely event it appears on land,

830
01:16:34,882 --> 01:16:36:000
we can anger it with gunfire

831
01:16:36:000 --> 01:16:37,426
and lure it back to Sagami Bay.

831
01:16:38,052 --> 01:16:39,165
After they were disarmed,

832
01:16:39,165 --> 01:16:40,570
all of them were burned down,

832
01:16:40,570 --> 01:16:40,971
the Japanese fighter jets.

832
01:16:41,597 --> 01:16:43,253
Even if there were some left,

833
01:16:43,253 --> 01:16:45,309
it breathes Heat Rays.

833
01:16:45,392 --> 01:16:47,489
Guiding it with an aircraft would be

834
01:16:47,489 --> 01:16:48,229
a very dangerous job.

834
01:16:48,312 --> 01:16:50,314
I don't care if it's dangerous.

835
01:16:50,397 --> 01:16:54,068
Fighter jets are more mobile than ships anyways.

836
01:16:54,151 --> 01:16:57,071
Are you aiming to get shot down on purpose?

837
01:16:57,154 --> 01:16:58,836
Are you just...

838
01:16:58,836 --> 01:17:00,449
Desperate?

838
01:17:02,320 --> 01:17:02,952
Are you drunk?

839
01:17:03,536 --> 01:17:05,996
You just want to avenge Nori-chan.

840
01:17:07,164 --> 01:17:08,249
And you've got a problem with that, don't you?

841
01:17:08,332 --> 01:17:10,292
Now that...

842
01:17:12,461 --> 01:17:13,775
Why didn't you take Nori-chan as your wife

843
01:17:13,775 --> 01:17:16,173
before all this happened?

843
01:17:16,257 --> 01:17:18,050
You knew how she felt about it, didn't you?

844
01:17:18,134 --> 01:17:20,886
I wanted to do that too!

845
01:17:21,971 --> 01:17:23,973
So why?

846
01:17:26,058 --> 01:17:27,101
My...

847
01:17:33,816 --> 01:17:36,026
war hasn't ended.

848
01:18:01,343 --> 01:18:02,970
There were fighter jets?

849
01:18:03,053 --> 01:18:05,890
Yep, but it's a very special one...

850
01:18:25,201 --> 01:18:27,600
It's a local fighter jet designed

851
01:18:27,600 --> 01:18:29,150
near the end of the war

851
01:18:29,150 --> 01:18:30,247
called The Shinden.

851
01:18:31,457 --> 01:18:33,959
Specially designed for hit-and-run bombing attacks.

852
01:18:34,043 --> 01:18:36,045
The maximum speed is over 400 knots.

853
01:18:36,712 --> 01:18:38,163
It has a canard design,

854
01:18:38,163 --> 01:18:39,423
and it's equipped with four 30mm guns.

854
01:18:39,506 --> 01:18:42,179
It's an innovative aircraft

855
01:18:42,179 --> 01:18:43,752
that boasts exceptional weaponary

855
01:18:43,752 --> 01:18:45,387
and incorporates many new inventions.

855
01:18:46,388 --> 01:18:47,874
Apparently, only a few prototypes

856
01:18:47,874 --> 01:18:49,934
were ever actually deployed in combat.

856
01:18:50,434 --> 01:18:51,925
They were deployed here

857
01:18:51,925 --> 01:18:53,892
for the final battle on the mainland,

857
01:18:53,892 --> 01:18:55:190
but they were forgotten about

857
01:18:55:190 --> 01:18:56,857
in the confusion after the war.

857
01:18:57,608 --> 01:19:00,720
Since it was left unattended for so long,

858
01:19:00,720 --> 01:19:01,570
the aircraft often goes rattle-rattle.

858
01:19:02,738 --> 01:19:05,157
I can't fly it like this...

859
01:19:05,241 --> 01:19:06,700
That's the problem.

860
01:19:06,784 --> 01:19:08,327
A good mechanic...

861
01:19:08,410 --> 01:19:09,621
No...

862
01:19:09,621 --> 01:19:11,100
A person who can repair this aircraft

862
01:19:11,100 --> 01:19:12,331
is what we need.

862
01:19:14,833 --> 01:19:18,462
I have a person in mind.

863
01:19:21,090 --> 01:19:25,511
Former Ōdo Island Mechanic Tachibana Sōsaku-san?

864
01:19:25,594 --> 01:19:26,512
Yes.

865
01:19:26,595 --> 01:19:29,390
Tachibana, Tachibana, Tachibana, Tachibana...

866
01:19:30,890 --> 01:19:33,227
He currently doesn't have an address registered.

867
01:19:33,310 --> 01:19:34,228
I see.

868
01:19:34,311 --> 01:19:37,439
We get tons of requests to look for people every day.

869
01:19:37,523 --> 01:19:39,692
It'll take a while for us to find him.

870
01:19:39,775 --> 01:19:42,611
I need to talk to him about some very urgent matters!

871
01:19:42,695 --> 01:19:44:180
You're in a difficult situation.

871
01:19:44:180 --> 01:19:45,572
Even if you say that...

872
01:19:45,656 --> 01:19:46,530
Please!

873
01:19:46,879 --> 01:19:47,700
Just do it!

873
01:19:47,783 --> 01:19:50,119
The survival of the country depends on it!

874
01:19:50,202 --> 01:19:51,833
Even if that's true,

875
01:19:51,833 --> 01:19:53,580
I can't do what's not possible.

875
01:19:53,664 --> 01:19:54,498
I'm sorry.

876
01:19:54,581 --> 01:19:55,916
Well then...

877
01:19:56,750 --> 01:19:58,419
Do you know which unit Tachibana belonged to

878
01:19:58,419 --> 01:20:01,422
before he switched over to Ōdo Island?

878
01:20:08,887 --> 01:20:11,140
I'm doing all that I can...

879
01:20:11,223 --> 01:20:15,394
But I can't get in touch with Tachibana-san.

880
01:20:16,603 --> 01:20:17,682
There are many other excellent

881
01:20:17,682 --> 01:20:19,315
former maintenance personnel.

881
01:20:19,398 --> 01:20:21,358
Why don't you just try a different one?

882
01:20:21,442 --> 01:20:23,110
Please give me a little more time.

883
01:20:24,820 --> 01:20:27,114
Why are you so obsessed with that person?

884
01:20:27,197 --> 01:20:29,283
There's no telling when Godzilla will return.

885
01:20:29,366 --> 01:20:31,285
It's no good if it's not Tachibana!

886
01:20:32,286 --> 01:20:34,288
He's gonna recieve my message soon.

887
01:20:35,622 --> 01:20:36,874
Please!

888
01:21:04,370 --> 01:21:05,700
Tachibana...

889
01:21:06,695 --> 01:21:08:583
Tachibana-san!

890
01:21:08:583 --> 01:21:09,239
It's you, Tachibana-san!

890
01:21:14,036 --> 01:21:16,038
What's the meaning of this?

891
01:21:19,708 --> 01:21:20,793
Ah!

892
01:21:23,253 --> 01:21:25,921
You're saying the deaths on Ōdo Island

893
01:21:25,921 --> 01:21:27,758
were all my fault?

893
01:21:29,802 --> 01:21:31,428
What's up with that?

894
01:21:32,179 --> 01:21:33,263
Sorry...

895
01:21:34,264 --> 01:21:35,870
I knew that if I said that,

896
01:21:35,870 --> 01:21:39,269
you'd get angry and come over here.

896
01:21:39,770 --> 01:21:40,813
Shame on you!

897
01:21:43,649 --> 01:21:45,651
That thing that attacked Ginza...

898
01:21:46,693 --> 01:21:47,694
was...

899
01:21:49,405 --> 01:21:50,864
Godzilla from Ōdo Island.

900
01:21:58,956 --> 01:22:02,876
Our fighter jets need to be upgraded.

901
01:22:02,960 --> 01:22:04,795
That way, I'll be able to defeat it!

902
01:22:05,671 --> 01:22:07,971
I really needed to meet up with you...

903
01:22:07,971 --> 01:22:10,384
so I could ask you do do that!

903
01:22:10,884 --> 01:22:13,512
That's why I sent the fake letters.

904
01:22:15,556 --> 01:22:16,849
Please forgive me!

905
01:22:22,729 --> 01:22:24,106
Do whatever you want.

906
01:22:25,566 --> 01:22:27,317
There's no way I'm gonna help you.

907
01:22:28,318 --> 01:22:28,900
Tachibana-san!

908
01:22:29,120 --> 01:22:31,238
Please wait, Tachibana-san!

908
01:22:31,780 --> 01:22:32,602
Please wait for a second!

909
01:22:33,000 --> 01:22:33,949
Tachibana-san!

909
01:22:34,032 --> 01:22:36,410
There's something I'd like for you to do.

910
01:22:36,493 --> 01:22:40,164
Something that only you can do, Tachibana-san.

911
01:22:42,082 --> 01:22:44,668
I once detonated a mine inside of Godzilla's mouth.

912
01:22:44,751 --> 01:22:46,628
It was far more effective than the guns on the Takao.

913
01:22:46,712 --> 01:22:49,360
He's weak to attacks from the inside.

914
01:22:49,360 --> 01:22:49,631
Do you understand?

914
01:22:52,092 --> 01:22:53,218
You...

915
01:22:54,636 --> 01:22:56,460
I'm going to take a fighter jet full of bombs

916
01:22:56,460 --> 01:22:57,890
and fly it into that thing's mouth.

916
01:22:57,973 --> 01:22:59,892
That will definently kill it!

917
01:23:06,857 --> 01:23:08,025
A suicide attack?

918
01:23:10,569 --> 01:23:11,841
Your war...

919
01:23:15,430 --> 01:23:17,326
...isn't over either.

919
01:23:20,537 --> 01:23:23,665
Ah, so you fell down?

920
01:23:23,749 --> 01:23:24,583
Ow!

921
01:23:24,666 --> 01:23:27,377
It's swelling up again pretty badly.

922
01:23:28,561 --> 01:23:31,381
It's a little embarrassing since I was drunk.

923
01:23:31,465 --> 01:23:33,509
I don't really remember what happened.

924
01:23:33,592 --> 01:23:35,200
Well, it's no wonder you were so excited after

925
01:23:35,200 --> 01:23:36,303
finding Tachibana-san, who you were

925
01:23:36,303 --> 01:23:38,764
very particular about wanting.

926
01:23:39,973 --> 01:23:41,975
A canard aircraft?

927
01:23:43,101 --> 01:23:45,604
I heard rumors about it, it actually was built?

928
01:23:47,940 --> 01:23:49,066
Tachibana-san.

929
01:23:49,858 --> 01:23:52,236
Everyone, thank you for coming!

930
01:23:52,319 --> 01:23:54,321
Are you Tachibana-san?

931
01:23:57,950 --> 01:23:58,586
Is this...

932
01:23:59,600 --> 01:24:01,828
The legendary local fighter jet Shinden?

932
01:24:01,912 --> 01:24:02,869
Yes.

933
01:24:02,869 --> 01:24:05,249
Can you fix it so we can fly it?

933
01:24:08,669 --> 01:24:11,004
We'll try everything we can.

934
01:24:11,505 --> 01:24:12,756
Thank you.

935
01:24:13,924 --> 01:24:14,697
Thank you.

936
01:24:15,960 --> 01:24:16,426
Thank you.

936
01:24:34,820 --> 01:24:35,946
What's wrong?

937
01:24:36,655 --> 01:24:38,570
If you make a face like that, planner-sama,

938
01:24:38,570 --> 01:24:39,533
it's bad for morale.

938
01:24:40,033 --> 01:24:41,952
I know I made this operation, but...

939
01:24:42,035 --> 01:24:44,123
I started to feel like it would

940
01:24:44,123 --> 01:24:46,331
take a miracle for the operation to succeed.

940
01:24:46,415 --> 01:24:47,749
Even so...

941
01:24:47,833 --> 01:24:49,138
The miracle won't happen

942
01:24:49,138 --> 01:24:50,836
if you don't do anything.

942
01:24:51,404 --> 01:24:52,379
That's true, isn't it?

943
01:24:53,171 --> 01:24:54,192
And look at that.

944
01:24:55,162 --> 01:24:55,924
They're smiling.

944
01:24:57,676 --> 01:24:59,553
They aren't idiots.

945
01:24:59,636 --> 01:25:01,300
They know well that this is a tough operation

946
01:25:01,300 --> 01:25:02,931
that risks their lives.

946
01:25:03,640 --> 01:25:04,600
Even so...

947
01:25:05,767 --> 01:25:10,314
Everyone looks so happy.

948
01:25:11,106 --> 01:25:14,026
Maybe this time, they can be helpful.

949
01:25:15,319 --> 01:25:17,446
Be helpful...

950
01:25:19,323 --> 01:25:21,700
We all survived the war.

951
01:25:22,451 --> 01:25:23,254
That's why I said,

952
01:25:24,530 --> 01:25:25,954
"this time."

952
01:25:41,136 --> 01:25:42,179
Hurry up!

953
01:25:45,724 --> 01:25:47,392
Please make room.

954
01:25:48,226 --> 01:25:50,169
1 hour ago,

955
01:25:50,169 --> 01:25:52,500
off of the East Coast of Hacijō Island

955
01:25:52,500 --> 01:25:56,151
at 33°10'N 140°01'E,

955
01:25:56,234 --> 01:25:27,901
It was reported that the installed Geiger counters

956
01:25:27,901 --> 01:25:59,780
have detected a reaction.

956
01:26:00,322 --> 01:26:03,867
And then here and here.

957
01:26:19,299 --> 01:26:20,926
Godzilla's approaching.

959
01:26:23,345 --> 01:26:25,430
Reverse-calculating from this speed,

960
01:26:25,514 --> 01:26:28,822
Godzilla will arrive at the trench off the coast

961
01:26:28,822 --> 01:26:29,810
Sagami Bay at 11:00 in the morning.

961
01:26:29,893 --> 01:26:31,436
In order to confront it,

962
01:26:31,520 --> 01:26:35,232
we will depart tomorrow morning at 8:00.

964
01:26:37,651 --> 01:26:38,527
However...

965
01:26:39,111 --> 01:26:41,488
Will the device be completed by then?

966
01:26:42,906 --> 01:26:44,866
Please take us with you.

967
01:26:44,950 --> 01:26:47,411
The three hours it takes to reach the site are precious.

968
01:26:47,494 --> 01:26:49,246
As an engineer, I want it to be perfect.

969
01:26:49,329 --> 01:26:49,971
But...

970
01:26:50,619 --> 01:26:52,916
You might get stuck in the fight with Godzilla.

970
01:26:53,917 --> 01:26:55,752
We all came back from the war too.

971
01:27:01,883 --> 01:27:02,631
Everyone,

972
01:27:03,516 --> 01:27:04,532
if possible,

972
01:27:05,011 --> 01:27:06,512
please go home tonight

972
01:27:07,300 --> 01:27:08,849
and spend time with your families.

973
01:27:10,475 --> 01:27:11,893
Are you saying to be prepared?

974
01:27:17,107 --> 01:27:18,400
If you think about it...

975
01:27:19,401 --> 01:27:20,183
If you think about it,

976
01:27:20,183 --> 01:27:23,989
this country has wasted too many lives.

976
01:27:25,115 --> 01:27:27,200
Tanks with vulnerable armor...

977
01:27:28,076 --> 01:27:30,379
Due to negligance of supplies,

978
01:27:30,379 --> 01:27:32,244
most deaths in battle

978
01:27:32,244 --> 01:27:34,166
are from starvation and disease.

978
01:27:35,667 --> 01:27:40,589
The fighters didn't even have basic escape methods,

979
01:27:42,299 --> 01:27:46,344
in the end being suicide attacks and gyokusai...

980
01:27:48,346 --> 01:27:49,973
So this time...

981
01:27:52,100 --> 01:27:54,291
I want to be proud of this civillian-led operation

982
01:27:56,635 --> 01:27:59,483
for not having a single casualty.

982
01:28:01,902 --> 01:28:03,954
The battle this time,

983
01:28:04,200 --> 01:28:06,281
It's not a fight to the death.

984
01:28:07,616 --> 01:28:10,118
It's a fight to live in the future.

985
01:28:14,539 --> 01:28:15,957
Let's do it!

986
01:28:22,881 --> 01:28:25,579
It's finally happening tomorrow!

987
01:28:25,579 --> 01:28:26,510
I'm trembling with excitement!

988
01:28:26,593 --> 01:28:28,136
You're not coming with us.

989
01:28:30,603 --> 01:28:31,556
What do you mean?

990
01:28:31,640 --> 01:28:35,018
Well, that arm isn't gonna do you any good.

991
01:28:35,644 --> 01:28:37,562
Shikishima's going too, right?

992
01:28:38,146 --> 01:28:39,940
Is it because I don't have any war experience?

993
01:28:40,023 --> 01:28:42,192
Do you really think I'm useless?

994
01:28:42,275 --> 01:28:48,156
Kid, you're lucky that you didn't go to war.

995
01:28:54,830 --> 01:28:56,915
I want to protect this country too!

996
01:29:00,418 --> 01:29:02,420
Why can't I come with you?

997
01:29:04,881 --> 01:29:07,884
We've been together for a while now!

998
01:29:09,511 --> 01:29:10,720
Please!

999
01:29:11,930 --> 01:29:13,515
Please take me with you too!

1000
01:29:14,224 --> 01:29:16,059
I want to go with you too!

1001
01:29:16,142 --> 01:29:18,728
I leave this country to you.

1002
01:29:18,854 --> 01:29:20,522
Captain!

1003
01:29:20,605 --> 01:29:22,065
Noda-san!

1005
01:29:52,596 --> 01:29:55,515
See you, Aki-chan.

1007
01:30:05,734 --> 01:30:08,862
Thank you for everything.

1008
01:30:22,292 --> 01:30:24,609
Akiko.

1009
01:30:24,609 --> 01:30:26,171
Did you have fun at oba-chan's house?

1009
01:30:26,254 --> 01:30:27,672
It was fun.

1010
01:30:27,756 --> 01:30:29,205
I see.

1011
01:30:29,205 --> 01:30:30,133
That's good.

1011
01:30:34,721 --> 01:30:36,014
Are you giving that to me?

1012
01:30:37,766 --> 01:30:38,850
Thanks.

1013
01:30:44,648 --> 01:30:45,815
Akiko.

1014
01:30:45,899 --> 01:30:46,858
Hmm?

1015
01:30:46,942 --> 01:30:51,071
Is this okaa-chan and me and you, Akiko?

1016
01:30:52,405 --> 01:30:54,574
Okaa's in it, too.

1017
01:30:55,825 --> 01:30:56,785
I see.

1018
01:30:58,411 --> 01:30:59,788
You drew it well.

1019
01:31:10,757 --> 01:31:12,842
Why are you making that face?

1020
01:31:17,597 --> 01:31:19,015
What's wrong?

1021
01:31:19,516 --> 01:31:20,558
Akiko.

1022
01:31:21,559 --> 01:31:23,436
Hey!

1023
01:31:25,480 --> 01:32:29,334
Hey, it's okay!

1024
01:32:29,334 --> 01:31:30,402
I'm not going anywhere...

1024
01:32:46,978 --> 01:32:48,271
Tachibana-san.

1025
01:32:50,231 --> 01:32:51,316
Can you deploy it?

1026
01:32:55,330 --> 01:32:56,279
I'll get it ready now.

1027
01:33:08,416 --> 01:33:09,751
The ordered bomb.

1028
01:33:11,336 --> 01:33:13,154
Two machine guns, 140 kilograms,

1029
01:33:13,154 --> 01:33:15,590
120 rounds, 80 kilograms, and...

1029
01:33:16,091 --> 01:33:17,104
One of the main fuel tanks,

1030
01:33:17,104 --> 01:33:18,468
400 kilograms, was removed.

1030
01:33:19,344 --> 01:33:21,288
Instead, this plane was fitted with a No. 25 bomb

1031
01:33:21,288 --> 01:33:23,848
in the nose and a No. 50 bomb in the fuselage.

1031
01:33:25,600 --> 01:33:28,103
Now, I can finally repay my debt.

1032
01:33:42,617 --> 01:33:43,827
It's funny...

1033
01:33:48,540 --> 01:33:50,542
I feel like I want to live.

1034
01:33:55,338 --> 01:33:57,799
Those who died that day felt like that too.

1035
01:33:59,050 --> 01:34:00,844
Everyone wanted to come back alive.

1036
01:34:02,512 --> 01:34:06:042
But their wishes weren't granted.

1037
01:34:06:042 --> 01:34:07,851
They were killed like insects.

1037
01:34:10,145 --> 01:34:11,229
I understand.

1038
01:34:34,502 --> 01:34:36,880
The kid who drew this is named "Akiko."

1039
01:34:38,882 --> 01:34:40,884
I want you to protect her future.

1040
01:34:45,346 --> 01:34:47,492
I'll kill Godzilla no matter what,

1041
01:34:47,492 --> 01:34:48,892
even if it means I have to kill myself.

1041
01:34:49,893 --> 01:34:51,978
It seems like you finally made up your mind.

1042
01:34:54,314 --> 01:34:56,671
All right,

1043
01:34:56,671 --> 01:34:57,942
I'm gonna tell you something important.

1043
01:34:58,860 --> 01:34:59,861
Look.

1044
01:35:01,196 --> 01:35:03,198
This is the bomb's safety device.

1045
01:35:03,907 --> 01:35:05,700
Pull it out right before you plunge into him.

1046
01:35:05,783 --> 01:35:06,701
Okay?

1047
01:35:08,870 --> 01:35:10,163
And...

1048
01:35:19,464 --> 01:35:21,466
Aki-chan.

1049
01:35:23,843 --> 01:35:26,429
What's wrong? Are you lonely?

1050
01:35:27,555 --> 01:35:28,556
Here.

1052
01:36:01,673 --> 01:36:03,883
Otō-chan...

1053
01:36:05,009 --> 01:36:06,552
Hmm? Otō-chan?

1054
01:36:07,428 --> 01:36:08,721
Otō-chan...

1055
01:36:09,555 --> 01:36:11,516
It's okay, it's okay.

1056
01:36:29,158 --> 01:36:33,663
This is Kuroshio 12, 35°03'N, 139°41'E.

1057
01:36:33,746 --> 01:36:35,456
A bunch of deep-sea fish emerging were spotted!

1058
01:36:54,350 --> 01:36:57,103
Godzilla spotted in Sagami Bay!

1059
01:36:57,186 --> 01:36:59,640
Currently, we are trying to use an underwater

1060
01:36:59,640 --> 01:37:03,359
loudspeaker to guide it to the area of the operation.

1060
01:37:03,443 --> 01:37:05,236
Advance schedule for each ship!

1061
01:37:06,946 --> 01:37:08,364
Let's hurry up and board the ship!

1062
01:37:08,448 --> 01:37:09,532
Let's hurry!

1063
01:37:12,076 --> 01:37:13,870
Looks like Mizushima-kun gave up.

1064
01:37:13,953 --> 01:37:15,538
I feel bad for him, but it can't be helped.

1065
01:37:15,621 --> 01:37:18,333
I actually don't want Shiki-san to fly either.

1066
01:37:18,416 --> 01:37:21,044
Isn't Shiki-san a suicide attack survivor?

1067
01:37:21,127 --> 01:37:22,086
Seems impossible.

1068
01:37:22,170 --> 01:37:23,600
Akiko is here.

1069
01:37:23,600 --> 01:37:25,298
He'll definently come back.

1069
01:37:35,350 --> 01:37:38,144
Underwater loudspeaker destroyed.

1070
01:37:38,227 --> 01:37:40,710
Godzilla has invaded Sagami Bay.

1071
01:37:40,710 --> 01:37:43,566
Wadatsumi Squadron, set sail immediately.

1071
01:37:44,233 --> 01:37:45,360
Hey!

1072
01:37:46,319 --> 01:37:47,487
Over there!

1073
01:37:47,570 --> 01:37:49,572
It's here already?

1074
01:38:00,583 --> 01:38:02,960
Godzilla breaks through the final defense zone!

1075
01:38:03,044 --> 01:38:04,462
Landing is imminent!

1076
01:38:05,296 --> 01:38:06,130
I'm leaving!

1077
01:39:01,436 --> 01:39:03,479
With this, you're going to end it all.

1078
01:39:04,814 --> 01:39:06,190
Shikishima.

1079
01:39:06,274 --> 01:39:08,526
Depart from port immediately.

1080
01:39:08,609 --> 01:39:11,965
Repeat, all ships of the Wadatsumi Squadron

1081
01:39:11,965 --> 01:39:13,364
are to depart from port immediately.

1081
01:39:19,620 --> 01:39:21,200
What should we do?

1081
01:39:21,200 --> 01:39:22,790
The plan's completely falling apart!

1082
01:39:22,874 --> 01:39:24,959
Even so, we'll still set sail.

1083
01:39:25,042 --> 01:39:27,700
The missles must be fired from the coast of Sagami Bay,

1084
01:39:27,700 --> 01:39:29,672
where they'll have the greatest effect.

1084
01:39:30,173 --> 01:39:33,426
All we can do is rely on Shiki-san to lure it.

1085
01:39:33,509 --> 01:39:34,510
Yes!

1086
01:39:34,594 --> 01:39:36,220
Let's do it!

1087
01:39:51,944 --> 01:39:52,669
Noda-san!

1088
01:39:52,669 --> 01:39:54,113
It's from Shikishima-san!

1088
01:39:55,781 --> 01:39:58,242
This is Shikishima, takeoff was a success.

1089
01:39:58,326 --> 01:40:00,495
Now luring Godzilla into the operation area.

1090
01:40:00,578 --> 01:40:02,622
We'll be ready soon too.

1091
01:40:02,705 --> 01:40:03,998
So let's get to the operation area quickly...

1092
01:40:04,081 --> 01:40:05,570
Shikishima!

1093
01:40:05,570 --> 01:40:06,876
Don't do anything crazy!

1093
01:40:06,959 --> 01:40:08,350
If you leave Akiko all alone,

1094
01:40:08,350 --> 01:40:09,212
I'll never forgive you!

1094
01:40:12,465 --> 01:40:14,300
Can you hear me, Shikishima?

1095
01:40:15,927 --> 01:40:17,929
Damn it, he's ignoring me...

1096
01:40:41,202 --> 01:40:43,079
Telegram!

1097
01:40:44,038 --> 01:40:45,039
Yes...

1098
01:40:51,754 --> 01:40:52,588
Yes?

1099
01:40:52,672 --> 01:40:54,173
Are you Shikishima-san?

1100
01:40:56,509 --> 01:40:57,343
It's a telegram.

1101
01:40:57,426 --> 01:40:58,386
Yes.

1103
01:42:23,402 --> 01:42:25,431
That's a big deal!

1104
01:42:25,931 --> 01:42:29,352
Godzilla's quite pissed off.

1105
01:42:29,435 --> 01:42:30,519
It's in pursuit.

1106
01:42:31,145 --> 01:42:32,647
It's our turn, isn't it?

1107
01:42:35,858 --> 01:42:37,234
All ships, prepare for battle!

1108
01:42:37,318 --> 01:42:39,862
All ships, prepare for battle!

1109
01:42:42,156 --> 01:42:43,407
Freon cylinders, all right!

1110
01:42:43,491 --> 01:42:45,159
46cm shells, all right!

1111
01:42:45,242 --> 01:42:46,535
Floatation device switch, all right!

1112
01:42:46,619 --> 01:42:48,162
Concentration cables, all right!

1113
01:42:48,245 --> 01:42:50,539
All circuits connected!

1114
01:42:50,623 --> 01:42:53,376
Checking power and releasing the safety.

1115
01:43:09,892 --> 01:43:12,353
All right, nice!

1116
01:43:14,063 --> 01:43:15,856
Unit 1, attack as planned.

1117
01:43:15,940 --> 01:43:18,234
As planned!

1118
01:43:49,306 --> 01:43:51,058
Nice!

1119
01:44:27,636 --> 01:44:28,510
That's...

1120
01:44:29,100 --> 01:44:30,347
Godzilla's Heat Ray.

1120
01:44:33,017 --> 01:44:35,311
It's impossible to do this type of thing!

1121
01:44:35,394 --> 01:44:36,489
Captain!

1122
01:44:36,489 --> 01:44:38,314
I recommend evacuating the ship right now!

1122
01:44:38,397 --> 01:44:39,690
No. This is good.

1123
01:44:39,774 --> 01:44:41,275
Please start the operation immediately.

1124
01:44:41,358 --> 01:44:43,194
But when will Heat Ray come again?

1125
01:44:43,277 --> 01:44:44,403
